Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.78,0:00:19.91,Song,Opening Song,0000,0000,0000,,It wasn't supposed to be \Nlike this, head in my hands
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.37,0:00:26.25,Song,Opening Song,0000,0000,0000,,Struggling to escape from \Nthis saturated world
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.84,0:00:32.01,Song,Opening Song,0000,0000,0000,,Time passes like whispering sand
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.55,0:00:35.72,Song,Opening Song,0000,0000,0000,,These circumstances, unchanging
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.72,0:00:38.72,Song,Opening Song,0000,0000,0000,,gazing out at a dreamless tomorrow
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.64,0:00:45.81,Song,Opening Song,0000,0000,0000,,Wanna say goodbye to the \Nconfusion of yesterday
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.19,0:00:51.23,Song,Opening Song,0000,0000,0000,,I try reaching out, as if to resist
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.53,0:00:56.95,Song,Opening Song,0000,0000,0000,,We cry millions of times \Nand then get born again
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.24,0:01:00.16,Song,Opening Song,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go with these red eyes
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.16,0:01:03.37,Song,Opening Song,0000,0000,0000,,to that pictured future
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.37,0:01:08.96,Song,Opening Song,0000,0000,0000,,Come here right by me, \NI'm clapping my hands
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.13,0:01:11.05,Song,Opening Song,0000,0000,0000,,Where are you? Who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.05,0:01:15.42,Song,Opening Song,0000,0000,0000,,Strain my eyes in the darkness
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.42,0:01:21.06,Song,Opening Song,0000,0000,0000,,Can't see anything, don't know \Nanything, but I'll still go
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.31,0:01:27.39,Song,Opening Song,0000,0000,0000,,To the place of shining \Nlight in which you wait
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.52,0:01:29.98,Episode Num,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,Episode Eight
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.52,0:01:29.98,Title,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,King of Paradise
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.52,0:01:29.98,Source,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,Inspired by Ango Sakaguchi's\NMeijikaika Ango Torimonochou\N(Meiji-era Detective Stories)\N"Foolish Apparition" and The Election Murder Case
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.90,0:01:33.36,Main Dialog,Customer A,0000,0000,0000,,The detective isn't back today, either?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.36,0:01:35.11,Main Dialog,Customer B,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder if something happened to him...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.11,0:01:38.41,Main Dialog,Inga,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry! Is there some \Nkind of case to solve?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.69,0:01:37.86,Name White,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\a5}Inga
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.69,0:01:37.86,Name Sub White,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\a5}Detective's Assistant
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.41,0:01:42.12,Main Dialog,Customer C,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't it about time the cucumbers \Non the roof were harvested?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.28,0:01:42.12,Main Dialog,Customer D,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Water is leaking through \Nthe walls again!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.12,0:01:44.20,Main Dialog,Customer E,0000,0000,0000,,My cell phone reception is lousy!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.12,0:01:46.37,Main Dialog,Customer F,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}I want him to give my food \Ncart's new dish a taste test!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.95,0:01:47.92,Main Dialog,Customer G,0000,0000,0000,,I need him to look for my precious \Nnecklace that I misplaced somewhere!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.79,0:01:49.04,Main Dialog,Customer H,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}How can I get back together \Nwith my girlfriend?!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.04,0:01:51.79,Main Dialog,Inga,0000,0000,0000,,Kazamori! Kazamori!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.21,0:01:53.55,Main Dialog,Customer F,0000,0000,0000,,I know! Since he's not \Nhere, you'll do, Inga-chan!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.55,0:01:56.72,Main Dialog,Customer F,0000,0000,0000,,How about working for me part-time?! \NIt's really not that shady a place!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.72,0:01:58.26,Main Dialog,Customer F,0000,0000,0000,,Just grilling yakitori \Nin a bathing suit!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.42,0:01:58.76,Main Dialog,Customer E,0000,0000,0000,,Inga-chan is a boy, you know!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.76,0:01:59.22,Main Dialog,Customer F,0000,0000,0000,,That's even better these days!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.47,0:02:04.26,Main Dialog,Inga,0000,0000,0000,,It's getting scary here... Come on, \Nhaven't you found Shinjurou yet?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.26,0:02:05.27,Main Dialog Italic,Kazamori (S),0000,0000,0000,,Don't squeeze me!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.27,0:02:07.18,Main Dialog,Inga,0000,0000,0000,,Sasa juice!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.18,0:02:08.44,Main Dialog,Inga,0000,0000,0000,,Where's Shinjurou?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.44,0:02:11.06,Main Dialog Italic,Kazamori (S),0000,0000,0000,,The firewalls are complex. \NI will attempt to retry.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.06,0:02:13.02,Main Dialog,Inga,0000,0000,0000,,Whatever, just help me!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.48,0:02:16.90,Name White,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,Sasa Kazamori
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.48,0:02:16.90,Name Sub White,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,Artificial Intelligence (R.A.I.)
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.21,0:02:35.63,Main Dialog,Kazamori,0000,0000,0000,,Shinjurou-sama! Shinjurou-sama!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.68,0:02:46.27,Main Dialog,Kazamori,0000,0000,0000,,Shinjurou-sama!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.72,0:03:26.10,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,"Mamori"... "Kaze"...?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.10,0:03:27.77,Main Dialog,Shinjurou (S),0000,0000,0000,,Kaza... mori...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.89,0:03:31.06,Main Dialog,Rie,0000,0000,0000,,Was he there?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.98,0:03:33.81,Name,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,Kaishou Rie
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.98,0:03:33.81,Name Sub,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,Kaishou Rinroku's Daughter\NLives at Home
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.31,0:03:34.27,Main Dialog Italic,Kazamori (S),0000,0000,0000,,I found him. He {\i0}is{\i1} in there...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.81,0:03:38.61,Main Dialog,Rie,0000,0000,0000,,The East Kantou Social \NRehabilitation Program Center...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.61,0:03:42.74,Main Dialog,Rie,0000,0000,0000,,Private-run or not, he's still \Ninside a prison. Shinjurou...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.74,0:03:46.83,Main Dialog,Inga,0000,0000,0000,,Shinjurou said he was being used \Nin that case with the codes.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.83,0:03:50.79,Main Dialog,Inga,0000,0000,0000,,And he was going to the privately \Nrun prison where that guy is.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.79,0:03:53.33,Main Dialog,Rie,0000,0000,0000,,A visit should only take an hour or two.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.33,0:03:55.75,Main Dialog,Rie,0000,0000,0000,,Why has he been gone for days now?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.75,0:03:57.29,Main Dialog,Rie,0000,0000,0000,,Can't we investigate further?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.29,0:04:00.63,Main Dialog,Rie,0000,0000,0000,,I have probably the most \Nsecure line in all Japan.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.63,0:04:04.89,Main Dialog Italic,Kazamori (S),0000,0000,0000,,A normal firewall couldn't mess with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.89,0:04:08.31,Main Dialog Italic,Kazamori (S),0000,0000,0000,,Because it's a part of me in the cloud.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.31,0:04:14.06,Main Dialog Italic,Kazamori (S),0000,0000,0000,,Still, there's an extremely aggressive, \Nunknown barrier around Shinjurou-sama.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.06,0:04:15.77,Main Dialog,Inga,0000,0000,0000,,You can't talk to Shinjurou?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.73,0:04:21.53,Main Dialog Italic,Kazamori (S),0000,0000,0000,,There's also something incomprehensible \Nabout Shinjurou's behavior.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.53,0:04:24.91,Main Dialog Italic,Kazamori (S),0000,0000,0000,,I stole this footage from \Na surveillance camera.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.79,0:04:34.79,Main Dialog,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,It's an honor to be called \Nupon by you, Chairman.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.79,0:04:37.75,Main Dialog,Kaishou,0000,0000,0000,,Well, Rie-san is all fired up...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.54,0:04:37.17,Name,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,Kaishou Rinroku
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.54,0:04:37.38,Name Sub,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,Chairman of JJ Systems
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.75,0:04:39.84,Main Dialog,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,Certainly, it appears \Nthat Yuuki Shinjurou
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.84,0:04:44.13,Main Dialog,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,is imprisoned in the privately-run \NEast Kanto Rehab Center.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.13,0:04:47.18,Main Dialog,Hayami,0000,0000,0000,,Even though he has no criminal record \Nand wasn't sentenced by any judge,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.18,0:04:50.10,Main Dialog,Hayami,0000,0000,0000,,the data shows that he's also \Nbeen given a prisoner number.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.10,0:04:53.64,Main Dialog,Hayami,0000,0000,0000,,It's possible that someone \Nhas falsified the data.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.06,0:04:53.68,Name,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,Hayami Seigen
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.06,0:04:53.68,Name Sub,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,Director of the Security Bureau \NMetropolitan Police Dept.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.06,0:04:53.68,Name,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\a5}Koyama Izumi
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.06,0:04:53.68,Name Sub,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\a5}Public Prosecutor\N Joint Coordinating Dept.\N Public Prosecutor's Office
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.93,0:04:55.48,Main Dialog,Hayami,0000,0000,0000,,What happened to him?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.81,0:04:56.31,Caption Top,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,Yuuki Shinjurou
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.56,0:05:00.65,Main Dialog,Kaishou,0000,0000,0000,,Well, why don't we just get him out \Nof there? Assuming he's innocent...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.07,0:05:02.94,Main Dialog,Head Maid,0000,0000,0000,,Please, Rie-sama! Don't go in there!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.32,0:05:07.82,Name White,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\a5}Kaichou Family Maid (Head Maid)
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.32,0:05:07.82,Name Sub White,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\a5}Kaichou Family Maid
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.49,0:05:07.82,Main Dialog,Rie,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going too!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.28,0:05:09.83,Main Dialog,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,Miss...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.83,0:05:13.20,Main Dialog,Rie,0000,0000,0000,,Please let me go as your \Nassistant, Izumi-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.00,0:05:16.08,Main Dialog,Hayami,0000,0000,0000,,An assistant and maid are \Ntwo different things.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.30,0:05:27.68,Main Dialog Italic,Kazamori (S),0000,0000,0000,,Please wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.55,0:05:30.18,Main Dialog Italic,Kazamori (S),0000,0000,0000,,I made these.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.27,0:05:34.85,Main Dialog,Rie,0000,0000,0000,,I'll take them.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.85,0:05:37.90,Main Dialog,Rie,0000,0000,0000,,I'll use them if the Detective resists.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.27,0:05:40.27,Caption Top,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,Visiting Room 1
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.02,0:05:44.74,Main Dialog,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,You attempted to incite the critic,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.69,0:05:48.03,Name,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\a5}Calls Himself a Novelist
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.69,0:05:48.03,Name Sub,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\a5}Prisoner
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.74,0:05:46.40,Main Dialog,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Yajima, to commit murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.40,0:05:48.36,Main Dialog,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,You call yourself "the Novelist", \Nbut your real name...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.36,0:05:52.20,Main Dialog,Novelist,0000,0000,0000,,When new characters are added to the \Nmix halfway in, the plot goes haywire.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.20,0:05:54.08,Main Dialog,Novelist,0000,0000,0000,,Just don't talk too much.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.08,0:05:55.91,Main Dialog,Rie,0000,0000,0000,,What did you do to the detective?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.91,0:05:57.37,Main Dialog,Rie,0000,0000,0000,,Who are those women?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.37,0:06:00.13,Main Dialog,Novelist,0000,0000,0000,,A murder occurred during a \Nmovie shoot at a movie studio.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.54,0:06:01.42,Main Dialog,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,Movie shoot?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.92,0:06:04.51,Main Dialog,Novelist,0000,0000,0000,,The murderer is cameraman \NYuuki Shinjurou.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.05,0:06:06.92,Main Dialog,Novelist,0000,0000,0000,,You're the high society female \Npolice detective, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.81,0:06:19.19,Main Dialog,Rie,0000,0000,0000,,Don't drag your heels!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.19,0:06:20.77,Main Dialog,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yes, ma'am!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.28,0:06:33.99,Name,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,Yuuki Shinjurou
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.28,0:06:33.99,Name Sub,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,Cameraman?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.28,0:06:35.62,Main Dialog,Hayami,0000,0000,0000,,Murder case?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.12,0:06:39.79,Main Dialog,Hayami,0000,0000,0000,,And Prosecutor Koyama has \Narrested the culprit?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.79,0:06:42.33,Main Dialog,Security Guard,0000,0000,0000,,It seems like everyone's up in arms.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.33,0:06:44.63,Main Dialog,Security Guard,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, I gather they're \Ngoing to investigate now,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.63,0:06:46.30,Main Dialog,Security Guard,0000,0000,0000,,so it'll probably take some time.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.30,0:06:52.14,Main Dialog,Hayami,0000,0000,0000,,The prosecutor just happens to be \Nthere with civilian Kaishou Rie,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.14,0:06:54.01,Main Dialog,Hayami,0000,0000,0000,,who I'm sure doesn't have the right \Nto investigate a criminal matter...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.60,0:06:56.52,Main Dialog,Hayami,0000,0000,0000,,It's like they're all \Ndreaming or some...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.43,0:07:00.98,Main Dialog,Hayami,0000,0000,0000,,A dream... I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.02,0:07:05.40,Main Dialog,Hayami,0000,0000,0000,,This is similar to the \NOono Myoushin case.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.40,0:07:08.90,Main Dialog,Hayami,0000,0000,0000,,The founder of a new religious \Ncult murdered his followers.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.65,0:07:13.12,Main Dialog,Hayami,0000,0000,0000,,The followers deludedly believed that \Neverything Oono said was reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.12,0:07:15.03,Main Dialog,Hayami,0000,0000,0000,,For example, they would \Nwatch a blank video
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.03,0:07:17.49,Main Dialog,Hayami,0000,0000,0000,,but "saw" whatever footage \NOono told them was on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.49,0:07:21.62,Main Dialog,Hayami,0000,0000,0000,,Oono had the power to make people \Nsee his words as reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.62,0:07:23.96,Main Dialog,Inga,0000,0000,0000,,That's the power of Bettenou.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.96,0:07:27.50,Main Dialog,Hayami,0000,0000,0000,,"Bettenou"! You mean the founder, \NBettenou, of Oono's group?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.01,0:07:29.88,Main Dialog,Inga,0000,0000,0000,,Bettenou is a kami.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.88,0:07:32.51,Main Dialog,Inga,0000,0000,0000,,She's like a deity with the power \Nto turn people's words into reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.51,0:07:37.31,Main Dialog,Inga,0000,0000,0000,,That's why I've been saying I \Nsmell her ever since we got here!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.85,0:07:40.14,Main Dialog,Hayami,0000,0000,0000,,All you said was that \Nsomething smells strange!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.39,0:07:41.56,Main Dialog,Hayami,0000,0000,0000,,But if you're right...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.10,0:07:45.06,Main Dialog Italic,Kazamori (S),0000,0000,0000,,This whole thing could be \Nsome kind of illusion...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.06,0:07:46.77,Main Dialog Italic,Kazamori (S),0000,0000,0000,,...created by Bettenou!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.11,0:07:49.57,Main Dialog,Hayami,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Hey! Give me my phone!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.77,0:07:49.57,Main Dialog Italic,Kazamori (S),0000,0000,0000,,She's showing her story to \NShinjurou and the others!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.57,0:07:50.74,Main Dialog Italic,Kazamori (S),0000,0000,0000,,Hopefully it'll be soon...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.74,0:07:51.99,Main Dialog Italic,Kazamori (S),0000,0000,0000,,Click!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.53,0:07:55.41,Main Dialog Italic,Kazamori (S),0000,0000,0000,,Maybe a little more?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.79,0:07:59.45,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,Kazamori!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.45,0:08:00.37,Main Dialog Italic,Kazamori (S),0000,0000,0000,,And one for the road!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.99,0:08:38.24,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,So this... is the mystery...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.75,0:08:51.17,Main Dialog,Sayo,0000,0000,0000,,Yuuki-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.26,0:09:00.18,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,Kazamori, I could've done \Nwithout that last one.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.18,0:09:01.81,Main Dialog Italic,Kazamori (S),0000,0000,0000,,Been a while, hasn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.81,0:09:03.68,Main Dialog Italic,Kazamori (S),0000,0000,0000,,What can you see right now?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.27,0:09:05.35,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,The truth, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.15,0:09:11.07,Name White,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\a5}Yuuki Shinjurou
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.15,0:09:11.07,Name Sub White,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\a5}Detective
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.81,0:09:10.27,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,Criminals, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.86,0:09:15.07,Main Dialog,Okamoto,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, the Metro Police Department \Nbrought it to my attention...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.07,0:09:19.07,Main Dialog,Okamoto,0000,0000,0000,,If it's made public that a person who \Njust came for a visit was imprisoned...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.78,0:09:23.16,Main Dialog,Okamoto,0000,0000,0000,,Right now, all we can \Ndo is leave it to them.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.16,0:09:25.46,Main Dialog,Okamoto,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Solving the murder takes priority.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.33,0:09:25.04,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,I found the scene of the crime.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.17,0:09:29.46,Main Dialog,Hayami,0000,0000,0000,,Are there shutters without \Nsafety systems these days?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.72,0:09:41.60,Main Dialog,Okamoto,0000,0000,0000,,It's been tampered with so that there's \Nno record of it opening or closing!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.60,0:09:44.06,Main Dialog,Okamoto,0000,0000,0000,,And the safeties aren't working either!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.57,0:09:56.86,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,A nonexistent streetcar doesn't run.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.86,0:09:57.86,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,This is the murder weapon.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.11,0:10:03.99,Main Dialog,Okamoto,0000,0000,0000,,This shutter separates the men and \Nwomen's blocks, so it usually remains shut.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.11,0:10:04.29,Name White,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\a5}Okamoto
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.11,0:10:04.29,Name Sub White,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\a5}East Kantou Social Rehabilitation Program Center\N Director of Security
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.99,0:10:06.96,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,Director Mitaka... I mean, the \Nsecurity guard, I guess...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.33,0:10:11.17,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,He would open this shutter every \Nnight to visit the women's block.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.92,0:10:14.34,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,To have contact with \Na female prisoner...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.80,0:10:17.17,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,That's why the line was cut.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.17,0:10:19.13,Main Dialog,Rie,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, who do you think you are?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.13,0:10:23.10,Main Dialog,Rie,0000,0000,0000,,What's the prime suspect doing playing \Ndetective and investigating?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.10,0:10:25.18,Main Dialog,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,It's just as my mistress says.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.18,0:10:26.73,Main Dialog,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,This young lady is the \Npride of the Metro P.D.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.73,0:10:29.06,Main Dialog,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,She solves cases with money, authority \Nand old-fashioned selfishness,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.06,0:10:31.11,Main Dialog,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,and they call her the Glamorous Gumshoe!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.94,0:10:35.07,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,I guess that novelist can't \Nwrite light novels...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.07,0:10:36.94,Main Dialog,Hayami,0000,0000,0000,,I'll go in myself and \Nconfirm the identity
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.94,0:10:38.49,Main Dialog,Hayami,0000,0000,0000,,of that man who's calling \Nhimself "the Novelist"!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.45,0:10:41.24,Main Dialog,Inga,0000,0000,0000,,And Bettenou, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.24,0:10:42.87,Main Dialog,Inga,0000,0000,0000,,I don't want to be held back anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.87,0:10:45.37,Main Dialog,Hayami,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? You intend to tag along?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.37,0:10:46.95,Main Dialog,Hayami,0000,0000,0000,,You think they'll let a kid in there?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.20,0:10:49.58,Main Dialog,Woman Inga,0000,0000,0000,,They wouldn't mind me, would they?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.87,0:10:53.46,Main Dialog,Woman Inga,0000,0000,0000,,As your assistant...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.88,0:10:55.96,Main Dialog,Hayami,0000,0000,0000,,S-Sure, why not?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.26,0:10:57.84,Main Dialog Italic,Kazamori (S),0000,0000,0000,,Leave the handcuffs on.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.84,0:11:02.85,Main Dialog Italic,Kazamori (S),0000,0000,0000,,Without the continued stimulus, you'll \Nbe swept up by the Novelist's tale again.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.85,0:11:05.68,Main Dialog Italic,Kazamori (S),0000,0000,0000,,Oh, and if they get too annoying...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.68,0:11:06.81,Main Dialog,Rie,0000,0000,0000,,Yuuki Shinjurou!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.81,0:11:07.22,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Like this?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.81,0:11:09.64,Main Dialog,Rie,0000,0000,0000,,How long do you intend to keep \Nup this ridiculous charade?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.52,0:11:14.90,Main Dialog,Rie,0000,0000,0000,,What have you done?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.90,0:11:16.32,Main Dialog,Rie,0000,0000,0000,,If you resist arrest,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.32,0:11:19.07,Main Dialog,Rie,0000,0000,0000,,I'll have you incarcerated for 780 years...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.82,0:11:19.74,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,I'm so scared...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.74,0:11:20.99,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,...he said, in a monotone.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.66,0:11:25.91,Main Dialog,Okamoto,0000,0000,0000,,The behavior of all the \Ninmates is monitored
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.91,0:11:28.66,Main Dialog,Okamoto,0000,0000,0000,,through their uniquely numbered chips.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.66,0:11:31.54,Main Dialog,Okamoto,0000,0000,0000,,This is in the area of \Nthe shutter last night...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.21,0:11:35.21,Caption Top,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,Yuuki Shinjurou
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.96,0:11:35.21,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,It's me...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.79,0:11:40.97,Main Dialog,Okamoto,0000,0000,0000,,Until the morning, no other number... \Nthat is, no other inmate was there.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.30,0:11:45.76,Main Dialog,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, you're the only \Npossible culprit, Defeated Detective!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.76,0:11:47.31,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,Why would I...?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.31,0:11:48.85,Main Dialog,Rie,0000,0000,0000,,I can picture it!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.85,0:11:52.14,Main Dialog,Rie,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure you said something like, \N"The truth must be revealed!"
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.14,0:11:54.23,Main Dialog,Rie,0000,0000,0000,,and got into an argument over it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.23,0:11:57.02,Main Dialog,Rie,0000,0000,0000,,You're a pro at pretending you're mean, \Nbut have a strong sense of justice.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.02,0:11:59.19,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,Are you praising me? Or dissing me?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.45,0:12:02.91,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,The numbers...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.91,0:12:03.78,Main Dialog,Okamoto,0000,0000,0000,,Do you have something?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.16,0:12:08.29,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,I was thrown in here by the man \Nwho calls himself the Novelist.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.54,0:12:13.12,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,But was it easy to issue a number \Nfor me, when I'm not a criminal?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.67,0:12:17.00,Main Dialog,Okamoto,0000,0000,0000,,The installed chips need \Na lot of maintenance,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.00,0:12:18.38,Main Dialog,Okamoto,0000,0000,0000,,so it's possible that a guard put it in.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.38,0:12:22.80,Main Dialog,Okamoto,0000,0000,0000,,But the monitored numbers are issued \Nby the court and public prosecutor.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.80,0:12:26.22,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, my number could've \Nalready belonged to another inmate,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.22,0:12:28.06,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,but was transferred to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.06,0:12:29.77,Main Dialog,Okamoto,0000,0000,0000,,That is a possibility.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.77,0:12:32.94,Main Dialog,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,Then there's another inmate \Nwith the same number?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.94,0:12:36.61,Main Dialog,Okamoto,0000,0000,0000,,Our security system would warn us \Nif two of the same number existed!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.61,0:12:39.15,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,Then even if he or she \Nhas the attached chip,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.15,0:12:44.32,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,one inmate here doesn't \Nhave a monitored number.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.32,0:12:48.33,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,That inmate can move about without \Nbeing seen by the security system.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.33,0:12:49.91,Main Dialog,Okamoto,0000,0000,0000,,There are surveillance cameras!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.91,0:12:51.75,Main Dialog,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,The victim probably changed \Nthe angle of the cameras,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.75,0:12:54.37,Main Dialog,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,just like he fiddled with the shutter.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.62,0:12:56.92,Main Dialog,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,So that no one could find \Nfault with his behavior!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.33,0:12:59.04,Main Dialog,Okamoto,0000,0000,0000,,I'll check on it at once!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.04,0:13:02.76,Main Dialog,Okamoto,0000,0000,0000,,The person who originally had \Nyour number is the killer!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.76,0:13:03.47,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.97,0:13:08.43,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,There was no war.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.14,0:13:13.27,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,If I solve this mystery, the dream that \Nthe Novelist gave us will disappear...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.94,0:13:19.94,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,I want the criminal records \Nof the female inmates!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.44,0:13:23.74,Main Dialog,Motoko,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder what'll happen to the movie...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.24,0:13:26.11,Main Dialog,Sayo,0000,0000,0000,,I just hope it doesn't get canceled.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.41,0:13:28.99,Main Dialog,Sayo,0000,0000,0000,,Right when it finally looked like we \Nwere about to accomplish something...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.99,0:13:31.12,Main Dialog,Sumie,0000,0000,0000,,We still don't know how it's \Nsupposed to turn out...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.49,0:13:33.25,Main Dialog,Motoko,0000,0000,0000,,Shinjurou-kun!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.13,0:13:45.92,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,The murdered Director Mitaka was \Nlooking for movies in the library.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.51,0:13:51.76,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,Stuart Rosenberg, Franklin \NJ. Schaffner, Frank Darabont.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.76,0:13:54.85,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,What do these three \Ndirectors have in common?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.85,0:13:55.68,Main Dialog,Motoko,0000,0000,0000,,They're foreigners!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.89,0:13:59.77,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,They all directed a famous \Nprison break film.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.77,0:14:00.86,Main Dialog,Sumie,0000,0000,0000,,Prison break?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.40,0:14:03.82,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,I saw the director...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.82,0:14:06.61,Main Dialog,Mitaka,0000,0000,0000,,You understand, don't \Nyou? You're Papillon!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.61,0:14:08.45,Main Dialog,Mitaka,0000,0000,0000,,No! Don't let go!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.74,0:14:10.53,Main Dialog,Mitaka,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Please! Don't let go!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.74,0:14:14.75,Main Dialog,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,He called the woman he was with \N"Papillon" and begged her not to let him go?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.53,0:14:11.87,Main Dialog,Woman,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Let go of me!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.37,0:14:16.96,Main Dialog,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,A problematic breakup?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.16,0:14:21.04,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,No. He wasn't telling \Nher not to let him go.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.33,0:14:25.38,Caption Top,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Note: Depending on the kanji, {\i1}hanasuna{\i0} can mean "Don't let go!" or "Don't talk/tell!"
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.04,0:14:23.25,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,He said, "Don't tell anyone."
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.25,0:14:28.09,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,The woman knew Mitaka's secret and he \Nwas telling her not to tell anyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.09,0:14:29.89,Main Dialog,Motoko,0000,0000,0000,,If the director had a secret,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.89,0:14:32.43,Main Dialog,Motoko,0000,0000,0000,,wouldn't it make more sense if \Nhe did the killing, instead?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.43,0:14:35.85,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,The reason the director snuck into \Nthe women's block every night
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.85,0:14:39.02,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,was to help the woman who \Nknew his secret break out.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.48,0:14:43.19,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,He looked to the movies to get a \Nhint for that, no matter how small.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.19,0:14:45.19,Main Dialog,Sayo,0000,0000,0000,,Break... out?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.19,0:14:46.99,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,It would be possible if a \Nmonitored number was switched
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.99,0:14:48.82,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,and you could get around \Nthe surveillance cameras.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.82,0:14:52.16,Main Dialog,Sumie,0000,0000,0000,,I don't understand. What \Ndo you mean by "break out"?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.45,0:14:57.87,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,I solved the mystery of your last lines.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.42,0:15:06.30,Main Dialog,Motoko,0000,0000,0000,,"That's right. I was just a NEET \Npretending I was some hacker."
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.55,0:15:07.92,Main Dialog,Motoko,0000,0000,0000,,What is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.51,0:15:15.39,Main Dialog,Motoko,0000,0000,0000,,"It was so much fun leaking the \Ngovernment's secret information,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.39,0:15:20.44,Main Dialog,Motoko,0000,0000,0000,,but when my blog started getting \Nattention, I started uploading lies, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.89,0:15:22.65,Main Dialog,Motoko,0000,0000,0000,,And then one day, the police came..."
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.98,0:15:28.94,Main Dialog,Sumie,0000,0000,0000,,"I had relations with an \Ninnumerable amount of people.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.03,0:15:31.61,Main Dialog,Sumie,0000,0000,0000,,It was because I was insecure...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.32,0:15:36.62,Main Dialog,Sumie,0000,0000,0000,,How long will the war \Nlast? It may never end...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.91,0:15:40.87,Main Dialog,Sumie,0000,0000,0000,,I wanted to be with somebody \Nso I could forget my anxiety.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.87,0:15:46.88,Main Dialog,Sumie,0000,0000,0000,,But when the war was over, I was \Ntold that I sold my body..."
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.97,0:15:59.02,Main Dialog,Sayo,0000,0000,0000,,I was an ordinary mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.60,0:16:02.10,Main Dialog,Sayo,0000,0000,0000,,My son wasn't even a year old
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.10,0:16:04.90,Main Dialog,Sayo,0000,0000,0000,,and I refused to let him \Nbecome a victim of the war.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.56,0:16:08.78,Main Dialog,Sayo,0000,0000,0000,,I just wanted to hold on to \Nmy ordinary everyday life.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.28,0:16:11.90,Main Dialog,Sayo,0000,0000,0000,,That's why I accepted my friend's \Ninvitation to participate
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.90,0:16:13.95,Main Dialog,Sayo,0000,0000,0000,,in a demonstration against \Nthe government...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.95,0:16:15.12,Main Dialog,Sayo,0000,0000,0000,,And eventually, I thought,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.12,0:16:18.83,Main Dialog,Sayo,0000,0000,0000,,"If that Prime Minister doesn't \Nquit, the war won't end...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.83,0:16:21.91,Main Dialog,Sayo,0000,0000,0000,,And if he doesn't quit, \NI'll make him quit!"
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.91,0:16:24.04,Main Dialog,Sayo,0000,0000,0000,,I researched how to make explosives...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.79,0:16:27.92,Main Dialog,Sayo,0000,0000,0000,,...and one day, the Public \NSecurity Force showed up.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.92,0:16:29.46,Main Dialog,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,During the war,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.46,0:16:33.51,Main Dialog,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,a number of terrorist bombing plots \Nagainst the Prime Minister were uncovered.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.51,0:16:37.10,Main Dialog,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,But terrorism by an average housewife \Nto protect her everyday life?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.10,0:16:39.06,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,During the war, Mitaka \NKichitarou also took part
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.06,0:16:43.10,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,in anti-government demonstrations, \Nwhich is where he met Izawa Sayo.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.10,0:16:47.77,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,But for him, the demonstrations \Nwere just a fad of the times.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.77,0:16:51.57,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,After the war, he became a guard \Nat this private-run prison,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.57,0:16:54.57,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,but if it became known that he \Nonce consorted with terrorists,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.57,0:16:57.12,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,he would lose his job, \Nhis future... everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.12,0:17:02.00,Main Dialog,Okamoto,0000,0000,0000,,So he switched Izawa Sayo's monitored \Nnumber and tried to help her escape!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.83,0:17:07.92,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,Mitaka asked me something...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.17,0:17:11.26,Main Dialog,Mitaka,0000,0000,0000,,Tanimura, Yada are \Nthere... and Izawa, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.01,0:17:15.59,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,At the time, you were standing behind \Nthat box, so he couldn't see you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.18,0:17:21.22,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,However, Mitaka's tablet displayed \Nthe inmates' numbers in real time,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.22,0:17:22.85,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,so even if he couldn't see her,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.85,0:17:24.98,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,it shouldn't have been \Nnecessary for him to ask me.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.39,0:17:26.85,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,So why did he ask?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.98,0:17:30.94,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,Izawa Sayo!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.53,0:17:34.45,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,It's because only your \Nnumber isn't displayed!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.57,0:17:43.20,Main Dialog,Sayo,0000,0000,0000,,He told me... He said he would get me \Nout of here if I didn't say anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.83,0:17:45.46,Main Dialog,Sayo,0000,0000,0000,,But I didn't understand \Nwhat he was saying.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.17,0:17:48.29,Main Dialog,Sayo,0000,0000,0000,,I'm shooting a movie.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.67,0:17:50.71,Main Dialog,Sayo,0000,0000,0000,,I should've been able \Nto film to the end...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.71,0:17:54.76,Main Dialog,Sayo,0000,0000,0000,,...and then I'd be able \Nto become my true self!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.63,0:17:58.18,Main Dialog,Sayo,0000,0000,0000,,So why do I have to be \Ncut from the movie?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.18,0:17:59.93,Main Dialog,Sayo,0000,0000,0000,,That's why I...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.02,0:18:06.23,Main Dialog,Rie,0000,0000,0000,,Even though he was trying \Nto get you out of here!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.23,0:18:09.65,Main Dialog,Rie,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe he felt sorry for you \Nbecause you have a child...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.65,0:18:10.48,Main Dialog,Sayo,0000,0000,0000,,No!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.48,0:18:11.57,Main Dialog,Sayo,0000,0000,0000,,It was the streetcar!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.57,0:18:13.90,Main Dialog,Sayo,0000,0000,0000,,It moved! It moved...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.90,0:18:15.40,Main Dialog,Sayo,0000,0000,0000,,It struck and killed him!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.40,0:18:17.28,Main Dialog,Sayo,0000,0000,0000,,War is a toy, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.28,0:18:18.66,Main Dialog,Sayo,0000,0000,0000,,And it isn't just me!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.66,0:18:20.41,Main Dialog,Sayo,0000,0000,0000,,It's you, too. And you!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.41,0:18:22.87,Main Dialog,Sayo,0000,0000,0000,,We've all made war into a toy!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.63,0:18:35.80,Name,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,Tanimura Motoko
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.63,0:18:35.80,Name Sub,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,Information Criminal
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.63,0:18:35.80,Name,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\a5}Yada Sumie
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.63,0:18:35.80,Name Sub,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\a5}Sex Offender
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.92,0:18:39.18,Name,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\a5}Izawa Sayo
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.92,0:18:39.18,Name Sub,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\a5}Terrorist
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.56,0:18:51.15,Main Dialog,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,Is it that frustrating having \Nto accept that this time
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.15,0:18:53.73,Main Dialog,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,Chairman Kaishou's \Ndeductions were correct,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.73,0:18:56.03,Main Dialog,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,and that Yuuki Shinjurou was innocent?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.03,0:18:57.28,Main Dialog,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,That's a terrible face.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.20,0:19:01.41,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, I'm going to stick \Naround here a little longer.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.99,0:19:04.91,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,I want to escape, but I \Ncan't pass up this chance...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.95,0:19:11.04,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,...to reflect upon myself \Nhere, at the terminus of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.88,0:19:28.43,Song,Ending Song,0000,0000,0000,,In the pale morning \Nmist, a whispered prayer
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.81,0:19:36.44,Song,Ending Song,0000,0000,0000,,I'm gonna follow this \Ntwisted landscape with you
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.90,0:19:44.45,Song,Ending Song,0000,0000,0000,,Looking for the "truth", \N"a 'lie' will do" is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.83,0:19:52.88,Song,Ending Song,0000,0000,0000,,Tracing it as if we can see through
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.88,0:19:56.75,Song,Ending Song,0000,0000,0000,,Looking for, beyond words
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.75,0:20:00.76,Song,Ending Song,0000,0000,0000,,Like a falling feather
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.76,0:20:03.76,Song,Ending Song,0000,0000,0000,,Looking for, find it
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.68,0:20:09.22,Song,Ending Song,0000,0000,0000,,So we can cuddle close together here
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.49,0:20:28.66,Song,Ending Song,0000,0000,0000,,Looking for, unravel it
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.66,0:20:32.75,Song,Ending Song,0000,0000,0000,,Like a tattered cloud
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.75,0:20:35.63,Song,Ending Song,0000,0000,0000,,Looking for, find it
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.46,0:20:40.80,Song,Ending Song,0000,0000,0000,,So we can cuddle close together here
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.60,0:20:52.81,Main Dialog,Novelist,0000,0000,0000,,Something's strange...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.81,0:20:57.56,Main Dialog,Woman Inga,0000,0000,0000,,Answer me. What do you want?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.56,0:21:00.53,Main Dialog,Woman Inga,0000,0000,0000,,What do you want with Yuuki Shinjurou?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.61,0:21:02.95,Main Dialog,Woman Inga,0000,0000,0000,,Resistance is futile.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.95,0:21:06.53,Main Dialog,Woman Inga,0000,0000,0000,,People have no choice but \Nto answer my question.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.87,0:21:11.37,Main Dialog,Woman Inga,0000,0000,0000,,Until then, you can't even \Ncall that mischievous kami!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.42,0:21:20.46,Main Dialog,Woman Inga,0000,0000,0000,,What do you want with Yuuki Shinjurou?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.01,0:21:24.17,Main Dialog,Novelist,0000,0000,0000,,He's my... Great Detective.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.63,0:21:27.72,Main Dialog,Novelist,0000,0000,0000,,I'm a novelist.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.72,0:21:31.06,Main Dialog,Novelist,0000,0000,0000,,I bring forth events onto the \Nsetting that is this reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.06,0:21:33.18,Main Dialog,Novelist,0000,0000,0000,,That's my novel.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.18,0:21:36.31,Main Dialog,Novelist,0000,0000,0000,,And my novel needed a great detective.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.60,0:21:41.15,Main Dialog,Novelist,0000,0000,0000,,I put him within my reach so \NI could polish my new work.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.73,0:21:43.61,Main Dialog,Novelist,0000,0000,0000,,I've thought of all the \Nplots I'll ever need!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.19,0:21:47.32,Main Dialog,Woman Inga,0000,0000,0000,,And so you had the guard \Ncooperate with you
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.32,0:21:50.16,Main Dialog,Woman Inga,0000,0000,0000,,in disguising Shinjurou as a prisoner.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.45,0:21:53.83,Main Dialog,Novelist,0000,0000,0000,,And then I had that guard disposed of.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.83,0:21:55.87,Main Dialog,Novelist,0000,0000,0000,,It's the detective's first case!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.37,0:21:59.34,Main Dialog,Novelist,0000,0000,0000,,But he shouldn't have been \Nable to solve the mystery.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.84,0:22:04.63,Main Dialog,Novelist,0000,0000,0000,,Because if he did, the pleasant \Nfantasy world would be destroyed.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.30,0:22:07.34,Main Dialog,Novelist,0000,0000,0000,,In this world of illusion,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.34,0:22:10.14,Main Dialog,Novelist,0000,0000,0000,,he embraced a mystery that \Nhe'd never be able to solve.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.14,0:22:12.89,Main Dialog,Novelist,0000,0000,0000,,He should've been mine!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.43,0:22:20.48,Main Dialog,Woman Inga,0000,0000,0000,,Too bad. There is no mystery that \NYuuki Shinjurou can't solve.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.48,0:22:24.15,Main Dialog,Woman Inga,0000,0000,0000,,Even if it means spilling \Nhis own blood...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.61,0:22:29.28,Main Dialog,Woman Inga,0000,0000,0000,,He always gives me the \Ntruth... the {\i1}souls{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.34,0:22:42.75,Main Dialog,Kaishou,0000,0000,0000,,What about Bettenou?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.34,0:22:45.92,Main Dialog,Hayami,0000,0000,0000,,You took her away, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.92,0:22:47.51,Main Dialog,Hayami,0000,0000,0000,,The way you always do...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.93,0:22:54.85,Main Dialog,Inga,0000,0000,0000,,"If someone hadn't killed him, \NI might've killed him myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.85,0:22:57.85,Main Dialog,Inga,0000,0000,0000,,Instead of going to all this \Ntrouble to look for the criminal,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.85,0:23:01.06,Main Dialog,Inga,0000,0000,0000,,I'd rather hunt down the \Nkiller of Takeda Shingen,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.85,0:23:06.15,Caption Top,Note,0000,0000,0000,,Note: Distinguished Daimyo in feudal Japan who has various stories surrounding his death
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.06,0:23:06.61,Main Dialog,Inga,0000,0000,0000,,who might've died of natural \Ncauses, suicide, {\i1}or{\i0} murder,"
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.61,0:23:09.78,Main Dialog,Inga,0000,0000,0000,,Shinjurou answered with a scowl.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.11,0:23:12.91,Main Dialog,Inga,0000,0000,0000,,Inspired by "Sneering Demon" \Nfrom Ango Torimonochou,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.91,0:23:15.91,Main Dialog,Inga,0000,0000,0000,,Next time on UN-GO: \N"Kaishou Rinroku's Crime".
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.91,0:23:15.91,Episode Num,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,Episode 9
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.91,0:23:15.91,Title,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,"Kaishou Rinroku's Crime"
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.91,0:23:15.91,Source,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,Inspired by "Sneering Demon" and "Red Trap" from Ango Sakaguchi's\NMeijikaika Ango Torimonochou\N(Meiji-era Detective Stories)
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.16,0:23:17.83,Main Dialog,Inga,0000,0000,0000,,There's a reason I'm so sherious...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.83,0:23:20.08,Main Dialog,Inga,0000,0000,0000,,I mean serious! I'm serious!
